@startuml current_004_save_load_roundtrip
title UC Life Sim — save/load round-trip (HEAD, SAVE_VERSION=4)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, sans-serif"

actor "caller\n(autosave / SystemMenu)" as C
participant "save/index.ts" as SV
participant "world Proxy\n(active scene)" as WA
participant "getWorld('playerShipInterior')" as WSHIP
participant "getWorld('spaceCampaign')" as WSPACE
participant "useScene + migratePlayerToScene" as SCN
participant "ecs/spawn :: resetWorld + spawnNPC" as SPAWN
participant "sim/loop :: stop/startLoop" as LOOP
participant "idb-keyval (superjson)" as IDB

== saveGame(slot) ==

C -> SV : saveGame('auto' | 1..3)
SV -> SV : refuse if clock.mode === 'combat'\n(transient state)
SV -> WA : query(EntityKey) →\n  snapshotEntity(e) per entity
SV -> SV : buildMeta(slot, gameDate)
SV -> WSHIP : snapshotShip()\n(Ship singleton + WeaponMounts)
SV -> WSPACE : snapshotSpace()\n(player ShipBody + EnemyAI)
SV -> SV : snapshotRelations(world)
SV -> IDB : set(bundleKey, superjson.stringify)\n+ set(metaKey, …)

== loadGame(slot) ==

C -> SV : loadGame(slot)
SV -> IDB : get(bundleKey)
SV -> SV : refuse if version unknown or seed mismatch
SV -> LOOP : stopLoop()
SV -> SPAWN : resetWorld()  // rebuilds every scene\n  // from data + seed
SV -> SCN : useScene.setActive(targetSceneId)\n  or migratePlayerToScene(target, …)
note right of SCN
  Bumps swapNonce → ScopedRoot
  remounts <App> with fresh
  WorldProvider, killing orphaned
  useQuery hooks left over from
  the pre-reset world.
end note
SV -> WA : index byKey via query(EntityKey)
SV -> SPAWN : spawnNPC(…) for missing immigrants\n(keys starting 'npc-imm-')
SV -> WA : destroy entities not in saved keys
SV -> WA : overlay each EntitySnap →\n  Character / Position / Vitals /\n  Health / Action / Money / Skills /\n  Inventory / Attributes / Bed /\n  Workstation / Job / Home /\n  PendingEviction / Reputation /\n  JobTenure / FactionRole /\n  Ambitions / Flags / …
SV -> WA : restoreRelations(byKey, relations)
alt v3+ bundle
  SV -> WSHIP : restoreShip(block)
end
alt v4+ bundle
  SV -> WSPACE : restoreSpace(block)
end
SV -> WA : mark every Character Active\n(loadGame auto-pauses, no\n activeZone tick to do it)
SV -> SV : useClock.setState(speed:0, mode:'normal')
SV -> LOOP : startLoop()
SV --> C : { ok: true }

note over SV,LOOP
  (CONCERN) save/index.ts couples to:
   - sim/loop  (stop/startLoop)
   - sim/scene (useScene, migratePlayerToScene)
   - sim/clock (setState)
   - ecs/spawn (resetWorld + spawnNPC)
   - getWorld('playerShipInterior'),
     getWorld('spaceCampaign')
   - systems/{combat, population,
     relations, engagement}
  Save knows every subsystem that holds
  module-level state. Each new such system
  costs save/load coverage. A "world reset
  lifecycle" event would invert this.
end note

@enduml
